05/04/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Romanian Defence Minister Teodor Atanasiu arrives in Greece on Tuesday (5 April) for a two-day visit. Talks will focus on issues related to bilateral military co-operation, regional security and ties within the frameworks of NATO and the EU. 
In other news, a meeting scheduled for Friday between Greek President Karolos Papoulias and Bulgarian counterpart Georgi Parvanov is being rescheduled, in light of Pope John Paul II's funeral that day. (ANA - 05/04/05; MPA - 04/04/05 
